week cultural immersion program in London to study the history and literature of Great Britain during the two World Wars  Dates  May 19   June 16  2016 Costs   6600 plus airfare and most meals subject to BOV approval Fees include tuition  insurance accommodation  outings  and breakfasts  International airfare costs are not included  Eligibility Any current student in good standing with an accredited university is eligible to apply  VMI students need only submit an application  Applicants from other universities should include a faculty letter of recommendation  an official transcript  and a short essay outlining the applicant s personal and academic goals for the program  along with the application  Applications must be received no later than 18 December 2015  Room and Board Students will be housed in dormitory lodgings provided by the American International University in London at its Kensington campus  The university will provide breakfasts  Academic and Cultural Program This will be a literature and history program in which all participants will earn three hours of ERHS and three hours of HI credit  The students will be enrolled in ERH 303WX  Cultural Rhetorics  Literature  Art and Remembrance in Britain WW I to WW II and HI 240X  Imperial Britain and the World Wars  1900 50  pending approval for the X designation for both courses and the W for the ERH course at this time  Students will visit several significant historical sites in and around London  such as Bletchley Park  Shakespeare s Globe Theater  and the University of Oxford  In addition to literary and historical studies  classroom time will be combined with on site research in various museums  including the British Museum  Imperial War Museum  and the Victoria   Albert Museum  Students will apply classroom discussions and readings to these on site visits to write enriched field trip reports and research essays on the First and Second World Wars in an imperial context  Program Director LTC Pennie Ticen earned her Ph D  at the University of Massachusetts  Amherst  She enjoys teaching classes on modernism and post colonial literature   Her current research centers on the use of the essay by post colonial writers such as Chinua Achebe and Salman Rushdie  MAJ John Matsui received his Ph D  at the Johns Hopkins University  He enjoys teaching courses on the American Civil War and the Atlantic World  In 2013 and 2014  MAJ Matsui received VMI Grants in Aid of Scholarship to further his research on missionaries and Empire in London   He is writing a book on religion and empire in an Anglo American context Academic Programs International Programs Home Study Abroad Online Application Study Abroad International Cadets Financial Assistance Passports and Visas Faculty Led Programs Independent International Travel Parents International Programs Staff Patricia Hardin Assistant Director P   540  464 7421 F   540  464 7768 E  International Programs Virginia Military Institute Old Hospital Lexington  VA  24450  Academic Programs International Programs Home Study Abroad Online Application Study Abroad International Cadets Financial Assistance Passports and Visas Faculty Led Programs Independent International Travel Parents International Programs Staff Patricia Hardin Assistant Director P   540  464 7421 F   540  464 7768 E  International Programs Virginia Military Institute Old Hospital Lexington  VA  24450 Academic Programs International Programs Home Study Abroad Online Application Study Abroad International Cadets Financial Assistance Passports and Visas Faculty Led Programs Independent International Travel Parents International Programs Staff Academic Programs Academic Programs International Programs Home International Programs Home Study Abroad Online Application Study Abroad Online Application Study Abroad Study Abroad International Cadets International Cadets Financial Assistance Financial Assistance Passports and Visas Passports and Visas Faculty Led Programs Faculty Led Program